# Local agent — goals to fully running, tested, vetted

Status: **draft 2026-07-06** — supersedes the Phase 7 tail of [[docs/ROADMAP.agent-toolchain]].
Target model: **`mlx-community/gemma-4-e4b-it-4bit`** (ungated, ~2 GB, multimodal-capable arch) — quality tier `gemma-4-12B-it-4bit`.

## Ground truth (verified on this machine, 2026-07-06)

| Fact | Evidence |
|------|----------|
| Current backend mistral.rs 0.8 (candle/Metal) **cannot load MLX-quant repos** | `tools/Cargo.toml` `agent-llm` feature |
| `google/gemma-3-4b-it` blocked — gated repo, HTTP 401 without HF_TOKEN | `dist/reactable-tools agent-status` |
| Weights already cached: Phi-3.5-mini (7.1 G), SmolLM2-360M (692 M) | `~/.cache/huggingface/hub` |
| Phi-3.5 runs offline end-to-end through `agent-chat` (`HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1`) | ok:true completion |
| …but ignored a "reply exactly PONG" system prompt → template/adherence unvetted | same run |
| `mlx-community/gemma-4-*` is **ungated** (`config.json` → 200, `model_type: gemma4`) | curl |
| mlx-lm **0.31.3** ships `gemma4` + `gemma4_text`; installed 0.29.1 does not | uvx probe |
| mlx-lm 0.31.3 needs **`transformers==5.0.0` exactly** — newer 5.x breaks import (`AutoTokenizer.register`) | uvx probe |
| mlx-vlm **0.6.4** ships `gemma4` + `gemma4_unified` (vision/multimodal path) | uvx probe |
| Rust MLX path exists (voice crates use mlx-rs 0.25) but `mlx-lm-rs` 0.0.1 implements **qwen3 only** — no gemma | crate source |
| gemma-4-e4b-it-4bit local generation **PASSED** — "Reply with exactly: PONG" → `PONG`, 52 tok/s gen, 4.27 GB peak mem | mlx_lm.generate 2026-07-06 |

## Engine decision (G0)

**Swap `agent-llm` from mistral.rs to a persistent MLX server process.**

- `mlx_lm.server` (OpenAI-compatible) run via uv with the pinned pair `mlx-lm==0.31.3` + `transformers==5.0.0`, managed as a child process (spawn on first chat, idle-timeout kill).
- Fixes the two worst defects at once: gated-Gemma dependency AND full model reload per turn (`llm_complete` currently spawns `agent-chat` → `TextModelBuilder::build()` every call).
- Keep `agent-chat --input/--output` contract; it becomes an HTTP client to the local server, so `api.work` barely changes.
- Later hardening (optional): port gemma4 to mlx-rs (extend mlx-lm-rs) for a fully self-contained binary. Not a blocker.

## Goals

### G0 — gemma-4 backend running ✅
- [x] T0 spike: `mlx_lm.generate --model mlx-community/gemma-4-e4b-it-4bit` → exact-instruction `PONG`, 52 tok/s, 4.27 GB peak (2026-07-06; weights in HF cache)
- [x] Sidecar-managed `mlx_lm.server` — persistent model, one load; pidfile + readiness + idle watchdog (`agent_llm.rs::ensure_server`); `reactable agent serve [--stop]`
- [x] `agent-chat` → localhost HTTP `/v1/chat/completions`; same JSON contract (`api.work` `llm_complete` unchanged shape). `enable_thinking:false` so short budgets land in `content`
- [x] Default `mlx-community/gemma-4-e4b-it-4bit`; `REACTABLE_AGENT_MODEL` overrides; 12B tier documented in verb doc
- [x] `agent-status` → 4 states `server-ready`/`model-cached`/`needs-pull`/`uv-missing`, **offline** (HF cache scan + localhost probe; server spawns with `HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1`)
- [x] `reactable agent pull` — explicit `hf download` with progress; chat path never downloads (errors → "run: reactable agent pull")
- [x] uv-pinned env (`mlx-lm==0.31.3` + `transformers==5.0.0`, py3.12) resolved on first spawn; HF_TOKEN/license/`REACTABLE_AGENT_BUILD` purged from verb doc, e2e script, `/agent` banner, Justfile, build-tools.sh, ROADMAP

